1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,962
<i>You know, Beth, not once</i>
<i>did Alice ever look down on you.</i>

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,797
<i>Do you know who did?</i>

3
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:07,298
<i>It was you.</i>

4
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:15,015
[ominous music sting]

5
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:16,016
<i>What's that?</i>

6
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:20,854
"I'M NOT DONE MAKING YOU PAY…"

7
00:00:22,355 --> 00:00:24,023
<i>- Is this Edong?!</i>
<i>- We thought</i>

8
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,775
Chloe just used it for a school project-

9
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,944
<i>- He got in here?!</i>
- [shatters]

10
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:40,790
[theme music playing]

11
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,152
[Erica] How's Yuri?

12
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:53,488
[Lucas] He's in a coma.

13
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,450
Do they really not
believe that Edong is still alive?

14
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:02,413
They refused to believe Erica and Lucas.

15
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:06,543
Even Ayoc's wife, who saw Edong
in the flesh, still won't saying anything.

16
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:13,591
I mean, can't we put up our
own wanted posters or something?

17
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:16,177
Independent from the police.

18
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,680
Not exactly wanted posters.

19
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:21,891
More on public notice
or request for information.

20
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:26,062
We can share a picture of Edong
to get information about his whereabouts

21
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:29,649
If someone sees him, they can contact us.

22
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:36,114
We can offer
a reward to entice people, right?

23
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:38,366
Would that be possible?

24
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,911
We can, but that might
encourage false tipsters.

25
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:43,288
And we have to be ready for that.

26
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:46,541
I'll take care of it.

27
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,710
Put my number as the contact.

28
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:52,881
Are you okay with that?

29
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:58,219
I don't want my
brother to kill more people.

30
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:08,229
Do you think we'll get
more information if we do that?

31
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,233
We have nothing to lose if we try.

32
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:16,779
Marco and I looked into
Louisa's murder case several times.

33
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,574
What about you and Alice?

34
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:21,701
Do you remember anything

35
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:23,870
that we might've missed?

36
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:27,624
What about Beth?

37
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:31,544
[pensive music playing]

38
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:34,047
It's fine.

39
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:36,382
We can do this without her.

40
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,260
I don't know if there's
anything else I can do to help you.

41
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:42,138
On the night Louisa died,

42
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:44,182
I looked for my brother.

43
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:45,600
[Lucas exhales deeply]

44
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:47,185
But I couldn't find him all night

45
00:03:47,268 --> 00:03:49,562
so I couldn't give him an alibi.

46
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,439
You were on the boardwalk all night?

47
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:55,318
Maybe you saw something else.

48
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:58,238
Since morning…

49
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:01,324
I kept looking for my brother.
I saw you guys were together,

50
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:05,119
I didn't approach
you because you were arguing.

51
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:06,871
Louisa and Edong.

52
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,001
[young Lucas] <i>So we're together now?</i>

53
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:15,546
[young Erica]<i> I like you.</i>

54
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:17,799
[Louisa] <i>Erica!</i>

55
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:19,384
<i>- Come here!</i>
- [young Erica] <i>Wait!</i>

56
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,594
<i>- Get away from her!</i>
- [grunts]

57
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,807
[Erica] While we were
waiting for Louisa at the time,

58
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,476
we didn't know she was
having a fight with Michelle.

59
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:30,645
<i>- You flirt!</i>
- [Louisa grunts]

60
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:32,897
- [Louisa] <i>Aah!</i>
<i>- You flirt! Damn you!</i>

61
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:36,943
[Alice] The reason why
Louisa kissed Romeo was because

62
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,862
she just wanted
to get a reaction out of Liezel,

63
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:41,406
who broke up with her that night.

64
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:44,784
[pensive music continues]

65
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:47,954
[Ken] <i>Hey!</i>
<i>Your friend got into a fight again</i>!

66
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:50,790
[Erica] When we went
to the area to look for her,

67
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,750
she must have by left then,

68
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:54,961
- because when we arrived…
- [thunder rumbling]

69
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:04,304
[pensive music continues]

70
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:08,599
[Alice] We kept
looking for her that night.

71
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,270
<i>No!</i>

72
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:13,438
[knife whooshes]

73
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,065
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa!</i>

74
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,027
[young Erica] <i>You monster!</i>

75
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:22,530
[thunder rumbling]

76
00:05:22,613 --> 00:05:24,198
[Erica] I saw
the scar on the killer's back…

77
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:26,242
The police didn't take it seriously

78
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:28,244
so they didn't investigate it.

79
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:30,997
Edong didn't have a scar on his back.

80
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:34,167
And now, it's clear
that Angelo has nothing to do with it.

81
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:37,170
[Lucas] What about Romeo?

82
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:40,298
He and Louisa got in an argument, too.

83
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:44,302
Shouldn't we question
everyone who has a motive?

84
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:46,387
[music turns unsettling]

85
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:49,182
- [Michelle] <i>You flirt!</i>
- [Louisa grunts] <i>Aah!</i>

86
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:50,475
- [Michelle] <i>Flirt! Damn you!</i>
- [Louisa]<i> Aah!</i>

87
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:54,187
[unsettling music continues]

88
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:58,441
Was there really no
evidence to find the killer?

89
00:05:58,524 --> 00:05:59,859
It rained that night,

90
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:03,696
which erased all
the evidence from the body.

91
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:07,950
[unsettling music continues]

92
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:20,338
[music fades]

93
00:06:20,421 --> 00:06:22,381
Then let's go to that Romeo.

94
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,509
[pensive music playing]

95
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:26,594
He's currently working in Dubai.

96
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,931
We can talk to Michelle Intal.

97
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,601
If you want to come…

98
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:36,938
Okay.

99
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,065
I'll talk to them.

100
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:44,278
Michelle knows me.
She'll be more open to me…

101
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:45,613
- [Alice sniffles]
- …than you.

102
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:47,615
[music fades]

103
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:48,908
Lucas is right.

104
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:52,787
Talk to any fire victims here in Amurao.

105
00:06:53,871 --> 00:06:56,874
It's possible that's where
Louisa's killer got their scar from.

106
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,252
[uneasy music playing]

107
00:06:59,335 --> 00:07:00,670
[Scott] How about hospitals?

108
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:03,005
Can we go there and ask for records?

109
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:06,217
We need a subpoena for that.

110
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:09,554
For now, we have
to ask for information informally.

111
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:12,974
Do you know where I can start?

112
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,020
I'll help.

113
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,648
Even if my wife doesn't want to.

114
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:24,360
[dramatic music playing]

115
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,746
<i>Why does he have this?</i>

116
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:39,917
<i>Remember, I noticed</i>
<i>it was missing before?</i>

117
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:42,837
<i>Don't you remember me asking you about it?</i>

118
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,381
<i>We thought Chloe</i>
<i>used it for a school project--</i>

119
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,632
<i>He got in here?!</i>

120
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:50,052
[dramatic music continues]

121
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,721
[Ryan] <i>We need to find that bastard.</i>

122
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:53,306
<i>If Erica and the others</i>

123
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:55,016
<i>are doing everything to find him,</i>

124
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,726
<i>then we'll do the same.</i>

125
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,063
<i>I don't want to be scared anymore, Beth.</i>

126
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:03,649
<i>I'm sick of it.</i>

127
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:07,195
<i>I'm sick of always</i>
<i>being at a disadvantage!</i>

128
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,238
<i>If he likes surprising us,</i>

129
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,324
<i>then we'll give him a surprise, too!</i>

130
00:08:13,117 --> 00:08:15,411
<i>Didn't you hear what I said to Alice?</i>

131
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,454
<i>I did!</i>

132
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:18,372
<i>I heard everything, Beth!</i>

133
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,333
<i>Even the things I shouldn't have heard!</i>

134
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:23,211
<i>Damn it, Ryan! Will you stop?!</i>

135
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:26,047
<i>I already told you I'm happy!</i>

136
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:27,632
<i>You're happy, Beth?!</i>

137
00:08:30,426 --> 00:08:35,014
<i>I asked you,</i>
<i>if you would still choose this life</i>

138
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,099
<i>if you were given the chance.</i>

139
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,602
<i>I answered, didn't I? I said yes!</i>

140
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:41,020
<i>Yeah! You did answer!</i>

141
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,397
<i>"Yes. Of course."</i>

142
00:08:44,398 --> 00:08:45,816
<i>Is that what you really wanted to say?!</i>

143
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,153
<i>Damn it! I could tell</i>
<i>you weren't being sincere!</i>

144
00:08:51,697 --> 00:08:54,784
<i>I don't know what you want me to say!</i>

145
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,827
<i>I don't know what</i>
<i>I want to hear from you either!</i>

146
00:08:56,911 --> 00:09:01,374
[dramatic music continues]

147
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:09,257
<i>Don't make me a fool.</i>

148
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:13,052
<i>I heard what you said to Alice.</i>

149
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:16,806
<i>But I won't let</i>
<i>that bastard step in here again!</i>

150
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:20,726
<i>What if he cuts off</i>
<i>our heads while we're sleeping?!</i>

151
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:23,354
<i>If you don't want to help</i>…

152
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:24,981
[music fades]

153
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:26,065
…<i>I will.</i>

154
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,569
[unsettling music playing]

155
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,320
Edong broke into our house.

156
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:32,863
What?

157
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:34,240
[Ryan] He took our family picture.

158
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,450
He sent it along with
the message he sent to Beth.

159
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:37,868
He threatened my family.

160
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,997
We need to catch
that bastard as soon as possible.

161
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,752
We don't need to find records

162
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:49,171
at the hospital or the police station.

163
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,549
There are a lot of
nosy people here in Amurao.

164
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:54,343
If anyone knows
who has a scar on their back,

165
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:56,637
it's them.

166
00:09:58,139 --> 00:10:02,602
[unsettling music intensifies]

167
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:07,648
- [Tom] Is she still freaking out, Auntie?
- [music fades]

168
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:10,693
My daughter had a rough night.

169
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:16,198
I don't think it's a good idea
to talk to her and make plans.

170
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:21,871
Mom.

171
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:27,251
You were right, Mom.

172
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:29,754
I've done it before.

173
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:32,423
I can do it again.

174
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:36,177
It's probably gonna hurt like hell.

175
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:38,012
But I'll do it.

176
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:41,849
[gentle music playing]

177
00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:44,268
[Mel exhales sharply]

178
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:45,811
Okay.

179
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:46,979
We're going.

180
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,606
Where?

181
00:10:50,024 --> 00:10:51,734
To take back what's mine.

182
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:53,402
[music fades]

183
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:56,447
Miss Vangie, how are you?

184
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,574
We just need something.

185
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:04,288
Miss Vangie,
there's something we'd like to ask you.

186
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:09,460
[sighs]

187
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:12,338
If only there was
someone who's as good as you.

188
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:13,714
[quirky music playing]

189
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:15,758
Vangie Corrales.

190
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:19,345
Amurao's Greatest Historian.

191
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:24,016
You know, dude,
there are a lot of vloggers in Amurao,

192
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,893
but Miss Vangie is on another level.

193
00:11:25,976 --> 00:11:28,521
I'm telling you, she knows everyone here.

194
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,147
- Is that so?
- Yes.

195
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:33,818
They might not know me, but I know them.

196
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:35,486
See?

197
00:11:35,569 --> 00:11:37,655
But why don't I know this one?

198
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:39,240
He's handsome. [giggles]

199
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:40,366
Uh, Marco.

200
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:43,119
Hi. Vangie. [chuckles]

201
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:46,580
Uh, Miss Vangie, he just has a question.

202
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:49,750
You can ask me anything.

203
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,627
Just don't ask me
how many pieces these are.

204
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:52,795
[chuckles]

205
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:58,509
Miss Vangie, do you know anyone
who was a victim of fire here in Amurao?

206
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:01,303
Someone who got severely burned?

207
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:03,514
A fire victim?

208
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,391
Yes, Uncle.

209
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,019
Do you remember what Erica said?

210
00:12:09,728 --> 00:12:13,691
She said she touched
the scar on the back of Louisa's killer.

211
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,318
She said it felt like burnt skin.

212
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:19,405
She told the police
about it several times,

213
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:20,823
but they never listened to her.

214
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:25,536
Well, we're investigating that right now.

215
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,329
[melancholic music playing]

216
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:30,124
So… you're investigating?

217
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:34,128
We want to find out
who really killed Louisa.

218
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,091
So…

219
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,136
You believe that Edong is innocent?

220
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:48,350
Of Louisa's murder. Yes.

221
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:50,102
But, uh…

222
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:52,396
The only reason he was convicted

223
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,357
was because of our false testimony.

224
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:59,570
[melancholic music continues]

225
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:05,201
And if everyone finds
out about what you did,

226
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:08,245
will you be okay?

227
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,208
We did something wrong, Uncle.

228
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:16,212
And now we have a chance to correct it.

229
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,673
We're gonna take that chance.

230
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:27,681
[music fades]

231
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:30,601
Hi, Uncle. Hi, Alice.

232
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:32,353
Hi, Althea.

233
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:34,855
Oh, good thing Althea's here.

234
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:38,692
She might know
someone like you're looking for.

235
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:41,445
Explain all the details
of who you are looking for.

236
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:43,989
A big fire…

237
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,158
here in Amurao?

238
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:47,660
Ah, yes.

239
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:51,997
Are there any survivors
who got a big scar because of it?

240
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,291
A scar on the back.

241
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:02,174
There is.

242
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:05,344
[pensive music playing]

243
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:09,515
Mario. He was Renata's
brother and Caesar's cousin.

244
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:15,187
His house burned
down when he was a teenager.

245
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:16,397
He was hospitalized.

246
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,524
He probably had a scar.

247
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:21,193
Where is he now? We need to talk to him.

248
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:23,988
He was buried at Campo Santo in Liwayway.

249
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:26,615
He died in the arms of his grandchildren.

250
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:32,288
They said he'd panicked
when he felt slightly unwell.

251
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:38,752
Well, he was about to receive
a cash gift of 100K in less than a month.

252
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:41,881
Ah… centenarian benefit.

253
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:43,966
He was 99 years old.

254
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:45,801
Negative.

255
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:47,636
Is there no one else?

256
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:52,224
[pensive music continues]

257
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:55,811
[music fades]

258
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,146
Damn it!

259
00:14:57,855 --> 00:14:58,772
There is?

260
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:00,816
That's what our government wants.

261
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,484
By the time we're old and sickly,

262
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:05,029
we won't even get to enjoy the benefits.

263
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:09,700
Meanwhile, Amurao's
congressman is only 22 years old!

264
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:12,745
And he's already stealing millions!

265
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:16,498
He doesn't even give us any aid.

266
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:20,628
His family was in
the market when the fire broke out there.

267
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:22,254
See?

268
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:25,466
[quirky music plays, fades]

269
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:34,475
Aah! OMG! Two big stars in
Amurao are here in my house.

270
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:38,562
Wait. Can we take a selfie? Is that okay?

271
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:39,897
[squeals] Wait a minute.

272
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,066
Alright, smile!

273
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,442
Oh, wait. Again.

274
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:45,069
[giggles]

275
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,780
Thank you. Yes?

276
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:51,158
Michelle, thank
you for agreeing to talk to us.

277
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:54,286
We just want to ask something
about the night Louisa was killed.

278
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,332
That was a long time ago.

279
00:15:58,874 --> 00:16:01,418
We just wanted to clarify
something about the night.

280
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:04,254
What is it?

281
00:16:04,338 --> 00:16:06,465
You and Louisa had a fight then, right?

282
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:09,009
[grunts]

283
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:11,720
[young Michelle] <i>You slut!</i>

284
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,847
<i>You're a whore just like your mother!</i>

285
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,058
[chuckles]

286
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:20,354
[laughs mockingly]

287
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:25,192
<i>Well, unfortunately for you,</i>
<i>your boyfriend like sluts!</i>

288
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,113
[sighs]

289
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:31,657
Can you blame me
for hurting her back then?

290
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,450
Your friend was a flirt!

291
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:35,536
May she rest in peace.

292
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,414
[Michelle] You have to understand.

293
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,666
She knew Romeo was my boyfriend.

294
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,877
And then of nowhere,
I caught them making out.

295
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,462
[pensive music plays, fades]

296
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:48,090
She was trying to make Liezel jealous.

297
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:49,425
[sighs]

298
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:52,052
Yeah.

299
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:53,887
I've heard the news.

300
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:56,765
Liezel has come out.

301
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,936
But, how was I supposed to know, right?

302
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:04,106
All I knew was
that Louisa was kissing my boyfriend.

303
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,108
Of course I lost it.

304
00:17:07,192 --> 00:17:08,986
She deserved that blow to the head.

305
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:13,157
[uneasy music playing]

306
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,659
[young Romeo]
<i>Michelle, what are you doing?</i>

307
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,202
- [Louisa yelps]
- [body thuds]

308
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,498
<i>Where's your tough-girl act now?</i>

309
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,666
<i>Come on.</i>

310
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,959
<i>- Let's go!</i>
- [gasps]

311
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:25,335
<i>How dare you!</i>

312
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:26,754
<i>Michelle, come on! Leave her alone!</i>

313
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:29,631
[grunting, breathing sharply]

314
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:30,716
[young Romeo]<i> Your bag.</i>

315
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:35,304
[unsettling music continues]

316
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:38,182
But… But she could still walk.

317
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:41,477
She didn't die after I hit her, okay?

318
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,561
[Michelle inhales deeply]

319
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:45,939
Before Edong was arrested,

320
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,901
I could hear everyone saying that…

321
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,863
it was me who killed Louisa.

322
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:56,200
But she was still alive when we left her.

323
00:17:57,618 --> 00:18:00,954
Did you notice anyone else when you left?

324
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:04,875
Someone who could've
been following Louisa that night?

325
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:07,753
No.

326
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:08,879
How about Romeo?

327
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:11,590
Romeo?

328
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:13,467
My ex-husband? [scoffs]

329
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:15,803
[scoffs] I'm no longer with that bastard.

330
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:16,970
Why'd you ask?

331
00:18:17,846 --> 00:18:19,598
Does he have a scar on his back?

332
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,935
- Scar?
- Yeah, kind of like…

333
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:24,812
burned skin.

334
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:27,106
[uneasy music continues]

335
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:29,149
I don't… He didn't have one.

336
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:33,362
Do you know anyone in
Amurao with a similar scar?

337
00:18:35,614 --> 00:18:37,449
[softly] No one at all.

338
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,286
- [music fades]
- [sighs deeply] Okay.

339
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:43,288
Thanks, Michelle.

340
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:44,581
[Michelle] Wait.

341
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:47,167
Can we take another picture?

342
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,253
I look bad in the last one. Is that okay?

343
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,839
Smile! Show me a smile!

344
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:54,049
Okay, cheers!

345
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,552
[Tim] <i>I was expecting</i>
<i>to see Anton's bodyguards.</i>

346
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:58,387
<i>Glad they're not here.</i>

347
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:00,889
<i>I mean, I brushed up</i>
<i>on my taekwondo moves.</i>

348
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:02,141
- [scoffs lightly]
- [snickers]

349
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:08,981
[tense music playing]

350
00:19:09,064 --> 00:19:10,858
[Glaiza]<i> Ma'am Mel…</i>

351
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:13,193
<i>Sorry, but you're not allowed in here.</i>

352
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:15,028
<i>Sir Anton would be furious.</i>

353
00:19:15,737 --> 00:19:16,864
[Tim] Excuse me?

354
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,575
Mel also owns this own house.

355
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:22,202
She's only returned to get her things.

356
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,745
<i>Why isn't she allowed in?</i>

357
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:24,913
[Glaiza sighs heavily]

358
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:26,999
Can I at least let him know first?

359
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,919
<i>Why does she need his permission?</i>

360
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,677
- [music fades]
- [Tim sighs]

361
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,724
<i>Remember when…</i>

362
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:46,143
<i>you and Jo saw…</i>

363
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:50,522
<i>the doorknob lying on</i>
<i>the floor and the bathroom door broken?</i>

364
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:51,690
[somber music playing]

365
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:52,983
<i>I said…</i>

366
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:55,652
<i>I don't know.</i>

367
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,529
<i>It suddenly fell last night.</i>

368
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,656
Yes, ma'am.

369
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:03,368
<i>And the day when…</i>

370
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,121
<i>I returned from the hospital</i>

371
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,875
<i>after passing out at</i>
<i>the Grace and Glam's fashion show?</i>

372
00:20:10,834 --> 00:20:14,379
<i>The same one when I said I just slipped</i>

373
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:16,506
and hit my stomach,

374
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:18,675
and the doctor said I had a bruised liver?

375
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:20,135
Remember?

376
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:22,179
- [whimpers]
- [Tim] <i>Mel!</i>

377
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,472
- [Anton] <i>Babe!</i>
- [Tim] <i>Mel?</i>

378
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:24,765
The truth is,

379
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:28,393
Anton destroyed
the doorknob and the bathroom door.

380
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,064
<i>I was hiding in the bathroom,</i>

381
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:35,817
<i>- afraid he would beat me up again.</i>
- [somber music continues]

382
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:38,278
And before the fashion show…

383
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:39,613
- [thud]
<i>- Argh!</i>

384
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:42,574
He punched me in the stomach. [crying]

385
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:46,370
<i>All because he didn't like me saying</i>

386
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:49,581
<i>that I could succeed without him.</i>

387
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:51,667
That's… what happened?

388
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:54,294
[cries, sniffles]

389
00:20:54,378 --> 00:20:56,213
[somber music continues]

390
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:58,006
You were all there.

391
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:02,052
I should've asked any of you for help.

392
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:04,429
[crying continues]

393
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:06,640
But I was terrified.

394
00:21:09,476 --> 00:21:11,436
I didn't want to show any weakness.

395
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:15,065
I didn't want to show vulnerability.

396
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:17,067
I don't want people to see any signs

397
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:19,069
that I was going through something.

398
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:24,241
So even when people called me mean…

399
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,493
bitch…

400
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:28,787
problematic…

401
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,039
toxic…

402
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:34,167
I just ignored all of it.

403
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:40,340
Because I wanted to keep that illusion
that I was in control.

404
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:42,843
[somber music continues]

405
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:44,928
- [sobs]
- But now…

406
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:48,890
Now, I want to live authentically.

407
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:54,229
And I can only do
that if I get my life back.

408
00:21:55,022 --> 00:22:00,068
So, you might think it's shallow
and dismiss them as mere things,

409
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:02,612
well, they're important to me.

410
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:06,283
They're part of who I am.

411
00:22:06,366 --> 00:22:07,951
So, please…

412
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,162
Please, let us in.

413
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:11,580
[both crying]

414
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:12,914
Yes, ma'am.

415
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:15,292
I'm sorry, we didn't know.

416
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:17,669
I'm sorry, ma'am.

417
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,881
[somber music continues]

418
00:22:20,964 --> 00:22:22,257
My god.

419
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,555
All of it was happening before our eyes,

420
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:30,682
and yet we had no idea.

421
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:33,185
We should've seen it right away.

422
00:22:33,268 --> 00:22:34,978
We could've done something.

423
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:37,647
[somber music continues]

424
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:39,107
I'm sorry, babe.

425
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:42,819
- Don't apologize. It's not your fault.
- I'm sorry.

426
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:44,613
Don't say sorry.

427
00:22:45,363 --> 00:22:48,033
I'm sorry,
I let myself be blinded by Anton.

428
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:50,744
[Tom, Mel sobbing]

429
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:52,537
I'm so sorry.

430
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,832
[Tim] I didn't know.

431
00:22:55,916 --> 00:22:58,126
- We had no idea.
- I'm sorry, Mel.

432
00:22:58,210 --> 00:23:02,923
[somber music continues]

433
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:07,636
Sorry, Uncle.

434
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:11,389
We have to go. Or else,
I'll be late for my therapy session.

435
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:12,516
[Edward chuckles softly]

436
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,227
Babe. Bye-bye.

437
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:17,479
Be a good boy to Aunty Althea, okay?

438
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:19,272
Yes, Mommy.

439
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:23,401
Althea, thank you so much
for agreeing to take care of Seth.

440
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:24,861
[Althea] It's no big deal.

441
00:23:24,945 --> 00:23:27,531
We, have become best friends, you know.

442
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:28,824
Right, bestie?

443
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:30,826
- [Edward chuckles]
- [Alice exhales softly]

444
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:33,620
And even though
you don't want to leave Seth here,

445
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:36,206
he's clearly having fun with us.

446
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:40,710
Because Grandpa Edward
and Grandma Christina…

447
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:42,879
are Seth's favorites.

448
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,589
- Right, Seth?
- Yes!

449
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:47,634
- Yes.
- [all chuckling]

450
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:49,302
[Alice] Okay, goodbye for now.

451
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:51,388
Take care. Come on, let's play.

452
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:54,099
Alice?

453
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:59,312
So you and your friends trying to find,

454
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:02,607
someone who had a motive to hurt Louisa?

455
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:04,025
[uneasy music playing]

456
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:05,193
Yeah.

457
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:08,989
Do you remember your old schoolmate? Kyle?

458
00:24:10,323 --> 00:24:14,578
Didn't you guys have
a major argument with him,

459
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:18,957
and didn't he also
have a fight with Louisa?

460
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:20,917
[uneasy music continues]

461
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:22,419
Yeah. But…

462
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:26,173
after our incident with him,

463
00:24:26,256 --> 00:24:30,051
he went to the United States,
so we never really considered him.

464
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:33,889
But he returned to Amurao.

465
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:36,892
What?

466
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:39,603
[hesitates] When?

467
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:41,605
If my memory serves me right,

468
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:44,900
they returned two years
after they went to the United States,

469
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:47,152
because he did something stupid there.

470
00:24:47,944 --> 00:24:51,907
His family kept it a secret
that Kyle was back in Amurao.

471
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,116
[chuckles dryly]

472
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:56,369
I only knew because
his parents went to my church.

473
00:24:56,453 --> 00:24:58,788
[music becomes ominous]

474
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:01,124
- [Louisa] <i>Let me go!</i>
- [young Kyle] <i>You wanted it!</i>

475
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:02,709
<i>You might've said no,</i>

476
00:25:02,792 --> 00:25:04,794
<i>but deep down you meant yes!</i>

477
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:07,214
So if,

478
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,508
if he came back after two years,

479
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:16,264
he would've been in Amurao
when Louisa was murdered.

480
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:21,144
[ominous music continues]

481
00:25:37,702 --> 00:25:44,209
- [heart beating loudly]
- [ominous music continues]

482
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:53,551
- [shouts in anger]
- [mirror shatters]

483
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:02,978
<i>I almost thought you weren't coming.</i>

484
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:05,897
- [Alice] <i>Kyle.</i>
- [Erica] <i>Kyle Sebastian?</i>

485
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:09,234
<i>He was here in Amurao</i>
<i>the night that Louisa was killed.</i>

486
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:11,528
[Louisa] <i>Everyone at school</i>
<i>thinks I'm a loser.</i>

487
00:26:11,611 --> 00:26:13,738
<i>- But you, you are different.</i>
<i>- So you think I'm special?</i>

488
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:15,740
<i>Because for me,</i>
<i>Louisa, I think you're special.</i>

489
00:26:15,824 --> 00:26:17,534
<i>No, he was in the US at the time.</i>

490
00:26:17,617 --> 00:26:20,537
<i>He and his family were here.</i>
<i>But they didn't tell anyone.</i>

491
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,915
<i>He had a good reason</i>
<i>to kill Louisa, remember?</i>

492
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:25,375
<i>- Kyle!</i>
<i>- You wanted it!</i>

493
00:26:25,458 --> 00:26:26,918
<i>I know you meant yes!</i>
